WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.000
♪ Who's gonna help when the danger overwhelms ♪

00:03.000 --> 00:05.000
♪ And the mysteries are piled high? ♪

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
♪ Who's gonna be around, never gonna let you down ♪

00:07.000 --> 00:09.000
♪ When you're on a wild ride? ♪

00:09.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ Your friends are always by your side ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek ♪

00:21.000 --> 00:24.000
♪♪

00:24.000 --> 00:27.000
[ Thunder rumbles ] Kelsey, let us in!

00:27.000 --> 00:28.000
It's scary out here.

00:29.000 --> 00:30.000
[ Thunder rumbles ]

00:30.000 --> 00:31.000
[ Both scream ]

00:31.000 --> 00:34.000
Um, hi, Mr. Neil.

00:35.000 --> 00:37.000
Sorry for screaming, sir.

00:37.000 --> 00:38.000
We were expecting Kelsey.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.000
Yeah, you're usually not here.

00:40.000 --> 00:43.000
I work, and I'm working from home today.

00:43.000 --> 00:45.000
Kelsey's upstairs.

00:45.000 --> 00:46.000
Whoa, hey!

00:46.000 --> 00:48.000
Shoes, jackets. You're soaking wet.

00:48.000 --> 00:50.000
Yes, sir.              Yes, sir.

00:50.000 --> 00:51.000
♪♪

00:52.000 --> 00:53.000
[ Sighs ]

00:53.000 --> 00:56.000
Guess we're not goin' in the creek today.

00:56.000 --> 00:58.000
Well, at least now you guys get to stay for dinner.

00:58.000 --> 01:01.000
Hey, Mortimer, I think you've spent enough time on that sock.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.000
[ Chirps ]

01:02.000 --> 01:05.000
Wow, Kelsey, you've got a whole library here.

01:05.000 --> 01:07.000
Where'd you get all these books?

01:07.000 --> 01:10.000
Most of them used to belong to my mom before she passed.

01:10.000 --> 01:12.000
But my dad's helped me add to the collection.

01:12.000 --> 01:15.000
Ooh, ooh! This was my mom's favorite.

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
She used to read it to me before bedtime.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.000
"Say Good Knight"!

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
Ugh. Mr. Bern: Aah!

01:21.000 --> 01:22.000
Dad, you okay?!

01:22.000 --> 01:25.000
Kelsey, quick, I need towels!

01:25.000 --> 01:27.000
Not wash cloths -- towels,

01:27.000 --> 01:28.000
but not the good ones!

01:28.000 --> 01:31.000
[ Grunting ]

01:31.000 --> 01:32.000
[ Man groans ]

01:32.000 --> 01:35.000
I should've fixed that stinking skylight last spring.

01:35.000 --> 01:37.000
My files are all wet.

01:37.000 --> 01:39.000
Dad? You okay?

01:39.000 --> 01:41.000
Me and, ironically, this photo of us

01:41.000 --> 01:42.000
on The Drencher will be fine,

01:42.000 --> 01:45.000
but dinner -- that's another story.

01:45.000 --> 01:46.000
Take a knee.

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
Kelsey, my brave knight,

01:48.000 --> 01:51.000
I have to fix this crack in our mighty castle's...

01:52.000 --> 01:53.000
drywall.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
I'm afraid I must task you with a quest.

01:55.000 --> 01:58.000
I need you to order dinner.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
It would be my honor, Father.

02:01.000 --> 02:02.000
Thanks, sweet pea.

02:02.000 --> 02:04.000
Here, take this 20 pence.

02:04.000 --> 02:07.000
And please, choose tastefully.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
Whoa.                      Whoa.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
I know you three can handle the task.

02:11.000 --> 02:14.000
[ British accent ] I will not fail you, Father.

02:14.000 --> 02:17.000
Wait, so your dad wants us to order dinner alone?

02:17.000 --> 02:20.000
That's kind of an adult thing, and, I mean, we're kids.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
[ Normal voice ] Ah-ah-ah. Correction.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
We're  big kids.

02:24.000 --> 02:27.000
I'm 8, you're 9, JP's tall.

02:27.000 --> 02:29.000
We can handle this. Behold!

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
The sacred drawer of menus.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.000
Bow to the drawer.

02:34.000 --> 02:35.000
Bow.

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
Bow to the drawer.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
♪♪

02:38.000 --> 02:41.000
We must choose between the five holy realms of sustenance

02:41.000 --> 02:43.000
within a five-mile delivery radius,

02:43.000 --> 02:45.000
and we got to pick quick

02:45.000 --> 02:47.000
because I think some of these places close soon.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
Okay, uh, what do you feel like eatin', Craig?

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
I don't really care. I'm just hungry.

02:51.000 --> 02:53.000
Ooh! Wings.

02:53.000 --> 02:55.000
Nah, too greasy. Okay.

02:55.000 --> 02:57.000
Uh, can't go wrong with a sandwich.

02:57.000 --> 03:00.000
Uh, we can make sandwiches any time.

03:00.000 --> 03:02.000
Okay. Uh, pizza!

03:02.000 --> 03:03.000
Everybody loves pizza.

03:03.000 --> 03:07.000
Yeah, but I just had pizza with my family last night, so...

03:07.000 --> 03:09.000
I thought you said you didn't care.

03:09.000 --> 03:10.000
Listen, how about I Larb Thai?

03:11.000 --> 03:12.000
It's Thai food.

03:12.000 --> 03:15.000
My dad and I order from here all the time.

03:15.000 --> 03:17.000
We have to order Khua kling lamb for my dad.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.000
It's super spicy,

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
and he makes the funniest face when he eats it.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
Wait, we're calling them?

03:22.000 --> 03:23.000
Like, we have to talk

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
to unfamiliar adults over the phone?

03:26.000 --> 03:29.000
Isn't there a way to, like, order online?

03:29.000 --> 03:30.000
Nah, this place doesn't have a website.

03:30.000 --> 03:32.000
We got to call.

03:32.000 --> 03:34.000
I-I don't think they're gonna take an order from three kids.

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
Nobody takes orders from kids.

03:36.000 --> 03:41.000
But what if we don't  sound like kids?

03:41.000 --> 03:43.000
[ Grunts ] Remind me why we're doing this.

03:43.000 --> 03:45.000
Uh, it helps me get into character.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
Ooh, it's ringing.

03:47.000 --> 03:48.000
[ Clears throat ]

03:48.000 --> 03:50.000
[ Deep voice ] Good evening, ma'am.

03:50.000 --> 03:53.000
I require an order of pad see ew with chicken,

03:53.000 --> 03:58.000
your finest larb, and the Khua kling lamb.

03:59.000 --> 04:00.000
And a side of rice.

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
Children, please, I'm on the phone.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
And a side of rice.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.000
And I need it delivered.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.000
Oh, dear.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.000
Guys, their delivery driver is stuck in the storm,

04:11.000 --> 04:12.000
and they can only do takeout.

04:12.000 --> 04:13.000
Abort! Abort!

04:13.000 --> 04:14.000
Abort!

04:15.000 --> 04:16.000
[ Groans, grunts ]

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
Uh, takeout's fine.

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
Bye. I love you. [ Groans ]

04:20.000 --> 04:22.000
Takeout is fine?

04:22.000 --> 04:24.000
It's raining whales outside!

04:24.000 --> 04:25.000
[ Normal voice ] I know! I panicked.

04:25.000 --> 04:27.000
You weren't there, Craig!

04:27.000 --> 04:29.000
Great, what do we do now?

04:29.000 --> 04:31.000
We pick it up ourselves.

04:32.000 --> 04:33.000
My dad is counting on us.

04:33.000 --> 04:34.000
He has trusted us with this quest,

04:35.000 --> 04:36.000
and I won't accept failure

04:36.000 --> 04:38.000
no matter how many pits cross our path.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.000
Will your dad even let us?

04:41.000 --> 04:43.000
Hey, Dad! We're gonna go get the food!

04:43.000 --> 04:44.000
Mr. Bern: Okay!

04:44.000 --> 04:46.000
Bring your pepper spray and a Taser!

04:46.000 --> 04:47.000
I don't have those!

04:47.000 --> 04:50.000
Just be careful, then!

04:50.000 --> 04:52.000
♪♪

04:52.000 --> 04:55.000
Here, Craig, take the money for safe keeping.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.000
Sorry, buddy, you'll have to sit this one out.

04:57.000 --> 05:00.000
[ British accent ] Protect Father while I'm gone.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.000
Mwah!

05:01.000 --> 05:03.000
[ Thunder rumbles ]

05:03.000 --> 05:09.000
[ Normal voice ] Now, it's time to pick up our food.

05:09.000 --> 05:10.000
This way.

05:10.000 --> 05:12.000
We'll head up here

05:12.000 --> 05:14.000
and go under the Falling Branch Tree.

05:14.000 --> 05:15.000
[ Gasps ] Ha!

05:16.000 --> 05:17.000
Up to your same tricks, I see,

05:17.000 --> 05:19.000
Falling Branch Tree.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.000
[ Applause ]

05:21.000 --> 05:22.000
This way.

05:23.000 --> 05:24.000
Over there.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
Whoa! Aah!

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
♪♪

05:29.000 --> 05:32.000
Are you sure Mudslide Mountain's the fastest way down?

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
Positive.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
♪♪

05:36.000 --> 05:37.000
Aah!

05:37.000 --> 05:38.000
JP! Whoa!

05:39.000 --> 05:40.000
[ British accent ] Squire!

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
Farewell, friends!

05:43.000 --> 05:46.000
♪♪

05:46.000 --> 05:49.000
[ Normal voice ] Remember, this is Splash

05:46.000 --> 05:49.000
Alley, so be weary of --

05:49.000 --> 05:50.000
[ Horn honks ] Car!

05:50.000 --> 05:52.000
Trash-lid shields up!

05:52.000 --> 05:55.000
[ Horn honks ]

05:55.000 --> 05:57.000
How much longer now? It's straight down

05:55.000 --> 05:57.000
the street.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.000
You see it? I think so.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
Hey, JP, do you mind moving over a bit?

06:01.000 --> 06:03.000
Sure thing. Aah!

06:03.000 --> 06:06.000
JP! Oh, I see it.

06:06.000 --> 06:09.000
My booties are all wet thanks to that puddle.

06:09.000 --> 06:10.000
That was no puddle.

06:10.000 --> 06:12.000
It was at least three ankles below sea level.

06:13.000 --> 06:14.000
[ British accent ] Can you walk, squire?

06:14.000 --> 06:16.000
I guess I can.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.000
I'll just have to deal with my wet socks the whole time.

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
Fear not,

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
because I always keep an extra pair of dry socks on me --

06:22.000 --> 06:24.000
sandwich-bag protected.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.000
[ Gasps ] [ Normal voice ] The money!

06:26.000 --> 06:28.000
♪♪

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
What -- What do we do?

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
We must cross the street.

06:32.000 --> 06:33.000
Cross it?

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
That street's got like 50 lanes.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
Oh, why'd your dad think we could handle this?

06:39.000 --> 06:41.000
Hey! Pull it together.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.000
My dad didn't  think we could do it.

06:43.000 --> 06:45.000
He  knew we could do it.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.000
Now, take my hand.

06:46.000 --> 06:49.000
Oh, mighty crosswalk, we ask for your guidance.

06:49.000 --> 06:52.000
Please grant us safe passage.

06:52.000 --> 07:00.000
♪♪

07:00.000 --> 07:01.000
Wow!

07:01.000 --> 07:03.000
Ah! Ha! Got it!

07:03.000 --> 07:06.000
Man, you were right. We  can handle this.

07:06.000 --> 07:08.000
Guys, I don't want to ruin the moment,

07:08.000 --> 07:10.000
but the little walky guy turned into a hand.

07:11.000 --> 07:12.000
The spell's wearing off! Move it!

07:13.000 --> 07:15.000
[ All shouting ]

07:15.000 --> 07:17.000
Aah!

07:17.000 --> 07:19.000
♪♪

07:20.000 --> 07:22.000
Yeah! Yeah!                      Yeah!

07:22.000 --> 07:25.000
[ Bell rings ]

07:25.000 --> 07:27.000
Here we are.

07:27.000 --> 07:28.000
Sorry, pick-up only.

07:28.000 --> 07:30.000
Our driver's caught in the rain.

07:30.000 --> 07:31.000
No, we don't have a jet ski.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
Yes, we tried calling the jet-ski place.

07:33.000 --> 07:34.000
They don't deliver, either.

07:34.000 --> 07:35.000
[ Sighs ]

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
Anyway, how may I help...you?

07:39.000 --> 07:41.000
I'm here for pick-up.

07:41.000 --> 07:44.000
Name. JP:

07:41.000 --> 07:44.000
[ Deep voice ] Pokoly.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.000
Neil Pokoly.

07:46.000 --> 07:49.000
Oh, yeah, the kids pretending to be adults.

07:49.000 --> 07:51.000
That'll be $19.29.

07:51.000 --> 07:53.000
Keep the change.

07:55.000 --> 07:57.000
Here you go.

07:57.000 --> 07:58.000
♪♪

07:58.000 --> 08:00.000
Whoa. Whoa.                      Whoa.

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
We really got the food.

08:02.000 --> 08:03.000
It's warm.

08:04.000 --> 08:05.000
Feel it.

08:05.000 --> 08:07.000
Wow, it is.

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
Let's... Set...

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
The table.

08:10.000 --> 08:13.000
JP, there's some cups hanging over there on the hooks.

08:13.000 --> 08:15.000
Craig, check the dishwasher for plates.

08:15.000 --> 08:17.000
♪♪

08:18.000 --> 08:20.000
And don't forget my chalice!

08:20.000 --> 08:23.000
♪♪

08:23.000 --> 08:24.000
This is so fun.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.000
Reminds me of this one time

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
I went to Texas to go see my grandma

08:27.000 --> 08:29.000
who really isn't my grandma.

08:29.000 --> 08:31.000
Kelsey: Where's the rice?

08:31.000 --> 08:33.000
Where's the rice?!

08:33.000 --> 08:34.000
Aah!

08:35.000 --> 08:37.000
How could you forget the rice?

08:37.000 --> 08:42.000
My palate -- I'll never taste [Echoing] again.

08:42.000 --> 08:46.000
[ Screams ]

08:47.000 --> 08:48.000
They forgot to give us our rice!

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
My dad can't eat his Khua kling lamb

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
without rice to soak up the extra spice.

08:52.000 --> 08:53.000
[ Sighs ]

08:53.000 --> 08:56.000
I can't believe after all the trials we faced,

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
we still failed the quest.

08:59.000 --> 09:00.000
Hmm.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
All hope is not lost yet.

09:02.000 --> 09:05.000
We can make our own rice.

09:05.000 --> 09:07.000
I've never cooked rice before, though.

09:07.000 --> 09:08.000
Do you think we can do that?

09:08.000 --> 09:10.000
[ Scoffs ] Are you kidding? We can totally do that.

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
Yeah, look at all we've done today.

09:13.000 --> 09:15.000
We can definitely handle this.

09:15.000 --> 09:18.000
♪♪

09:18.000 --> 09:20.000
Okay, the pot is now waterized.

09:21.000 --> 09:24.000
Okay, now we got to cover it and bring the water to a boil.

09:24.000 --> 09:25.000
I got a lid.

09:26.000 --> 09:27.000
Hmm. What's wrong?

09:27.000 --> 09:28.000
We're kids.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
We're not allowed to turn on the stove.

09:30.000 --> 09:33.000
Rats. You're right.

09:33.000 --> 09:34.000
Hey, look, it turned itself on.

09:35.000 --> 09:37.000
Okay, we have to wait for the water to start boiling,

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
so let's finish setting up the table.

09:39.000 --> 09:43.000
♪♪

09:53.000 --> 09:56.000
The rice is ready!

09:56.000 --> 09:59.000
♪♪

10:04.000 --> 10:06.000
[ All groan ]

10:06.000 --> 10:08.000
Hmm?

10:08.000 --> 10:12.000
Oh! My eyes are melting from the light!

10:12.000 --> 10:13.000
Dad!

10:13.000 --> 10:15.000
Wow, what a bountiful spread.

10:15.000 --> 10:18.000
Fair knight, once again, you have shown this old man,

10:18.000 --> 10:20.000
who is not that old,

10:20.000 --> 10:23.000
the depth of your ability and skill.

10:23.000 --> 10:24.000
Thank you.

10:24.000 --> 10:26.000
I assure you, I could not have done it

10:26.000 --> 10:28.000
if it weren't for my trusted companions.

10:28.000 --> 10:31.000
They really saved the day by making the rice.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.000
Uh, i-it was nothing.

10:33.000 --> 10:35.000
Gentlemen, although your initial inability

10:35.000 --> 10:38.000
to take off your wet shoes revealed your ignorance,

10:38.000 --> 10:39.000
this meal has proven

10:39.000 --> 10:42.000
you are both somewhat competent children.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.000
Thank you.

10:44.000 --> 10:46.000
Oh.                          Oh.

10:46.000 --> 10:47.000
Smile over.

10:47.000 --> 10:49.000
So, shall we digeth in?

10:49.000 --> 10:51.000
Yeah! Yeah!                      Yeah!

10:51.000 --> 10:52.000
Ooh!

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
Spicy!

10:54.000 --> 10:55.000
Kelsey: Dad, the rice!

10:55.000 --> 10:58.000
Mr. Bern: The rice. Ahh.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.000
[ Laughter ]

10:59.000 --> 11:01.000
And laughing over.

11:02.000 --> 11:04.000
♪ When it's time to go to bed ♪

11:04.000 --> 11:09.000
♪ I know I don't have to feel alone ♪

11:09.000 --> 11:12.000
♪ 'Cause I'll see you tomorrow ♪

11:12.000 --> 11:14.000
♪ At the creek ♪

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
Just like I drew it.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
♪♪
